# Remote Access

## Overview

This document describes how the lab is accessed remotely — from outside the home network — and how internal management access is structured between lab machines.

All remote access uses Tailscale as the secure overlay network. No ports are exposed directly to the internet.

---

## Remote Access Architecture

```
Internet (Alienware / any device)
        │
        │  Tailscale encrypted tunnel
        ▼
Ubuntu Server VM (Tailscale IP: 100.82.166.75)
        │
        │  ssh opnsense  (key-only, via 192.168.10.4 → 192.168.10.1)
        ▼
OPNsense Firewall (192.168.10.1)
        │
        │  lab network access (all VLANs via enp0s2 static routes)
        ▼
All lab hosts (VLAN 10/20/30/40)
```

