## SSH Access Patterns

### From Alienware (or any device) → Ubuntu Server

```bash
ssh homeserver
# resolves to Tailscale IP 100.82.166.75
# auth: SSH key only (no password)
```

### From Ubuntu Server → OPNsense Firewall

```bash
ssh opnsense
# alias defined in ~/.ssh/config:
#   HostName 192.168.10.1
#   User root
#   BindAddress 192.168.10.4
#   IdentityFile ~/.ssh/opnsense_key
# auth: SSH key only (ed25519, no password)
```

### From Ubuntu Server → Lab VMs

```bash
ssh user@192.168.30.20   # Metasploitable
ssh user@192.168.20.20   # Kali Linux
ssh user@192.168.30.10   # Windows 11 (if SSH enabled)
```

All lab VM traffic routes automatically via enp0s2 → OPNsense → destination VLAN.

