## OPNsense SSH Configuration

| Setting | Value |
| --- | --- |
| SSH enabled | Yes |
| Root login | Permitted |
| Password login | Disabled |
| Key-only auth | Yes (ed25519) |
| Listen interfaces | All |
| SSH port | 22 |
| Authorized key location | `/conf/config.xml` → `<authorizedkeys>` field |

> **Important:** OPNsense manages SSH authorized keys through its XML config, not
> through `/root/.ssh/authorized_keys` directly. Keys written to the filesystem are
> wiped on config save. Always add keys via `/conf/config.xml`.

---

## Firewall Rules Supporting Remote Access

The following rule in `vlan_10_management` enables Ubuntu Server → OPNsense SSH:

| Rule | Source | Destination | Port | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Allow SSH to firewall | 192.168.10.4 | This Firewall | 22 (TCP) | Ubuntu Server → OPNsense SSH |

